---
---

<div class="text-center">
  <span class="eyebrow">Choose your path</span>
  <h2 class="mt-5 text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-white max-w-3xl mx-auto">
    Three entry paths. One goal: become team-ready.
  </h2>
  <p class="mt-4 text-lg copy-muted max-w-2xl mx-auto">
    Start where you are right now. DEVS helps you pick the right starting path,
    then build workflow reps from there.
  </p>

  <div class="mt-10 grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 text-left">
    <div class="surface-card p-5">
      <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-wide text-[var(--color-accent)] font-semibold">Path 1</p>
      <h3 class="mt-2 text-lg font-semibold text-white">Never programmed before</h3>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm copy-muted">
        Full beginner coverage: fundamentals, tooling, Git/PR flow, and team
        communication.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="surface-card p-5">
      <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-wide text-[var(--color-accent)] font-semibold">Path 2</p>
      <h3 class="mt-2 text-lg font-semibold text-white">You can code already</h3>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm copy-muted">
        Convert language knowledge into real team execution: reviews, sprints,
        quality gates, and delivery habits.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="surface-card p-5">
      <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-wide text-[var(--color-accent)] font-semibold">Path 3</p>
      <h3 class="mt-2 text-lg font-semibold text-white">You have team experience</h3>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm copy-muted">
        Practice reps in labs to improve review quality, delivery consistency,
        and modern AI-assisted execution speed.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <p class="mt-6 text-sm copy-muted max-w-2xl mx-auto">
    All paths can start in <span class="text-[var(--color-accent)] font-semibold">Free Core</span> with one structured flow. Pro is optional and adds guided check-ins, expanded curated lab tracks, and faster feedback.
  </p>

  <p class="mt-8 text-xs copy-subtle max-w-xl mx-auto">
    CS grad • 8+ years in software, including 4+ years in hands-on developer roles. Built around what I wish school taught before day one.
  </p>
</div>
